### Portfolio API Tests
### Make sure your Spring Boot app is running on localhost:8080

### 1. GET all portfolio items
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio

###

### 2. POST new portfolio item (AAPL)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "AAPL",
  "quantity": 100,
  "buyPrice": 150.50,
  "buyDate": "2025-07-28"
}

###

### 3. POST another item (GOOGL)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "GOOGL",
  "quantity": 50,
  "buyPrice": 2800.00,
  "buyDate": "2025-07-28"
}

###

### 4. GET all items (should show 2 items)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio

###

### 5. GET specific item
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio/1

###

### 6. PUT (update) item
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantity": 150,
  "buyPrice": 155.75,
  "buyDate": "2025-07-25"
}

###

### 7. GET all items again (should show updated item)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio

###

### 8. DELETE item
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio/1

###

### 9. GET all items (should show 1 item remaining)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio

###

### 10. Test error case - POST with invalid data
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "",
  "quantity": -5,
  "buyPrice": -10.00
}

###

### 11. Test error case - GET non-existent item
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolio/999 


